Four orange lights. At first mistook them for stars. Faded one by one

Light in the sky. Other lights falling or dripping from it to the ground.

15 fireballs in the sky. Not aircraft.

Same as the UFO seen over the House of Commons in February

Six red or orange lights in a large oval shape moving slowly towards

A blue and purple flashing light over the moors for 30 minutes.

Bright orange lights continuously going up and down on the horizon.

An orange/yellow object moving NW to SE. Followed by three more.

A bright orange object. The top was rounded like the top of a balloon

Two orange lights in the sky that hovered over the old hospital site.

A bright light that went straight up in the sky above the A12 near

Two strange lights behind the clouds that appeared to be playing

A single object the size of a large car. Silver with flames flickering

80 bright lights over the top of Queen's Hill in Swindon.

A ball of light in the clouds, moving slowly and falling apart. Had

A very bright object that glows red and bright.

Bright orange object travelling west to east across the sky.

Various different lights in a star shape.

An object in the sky changing colour.

An object hovering in the sky. The object had bright lights.

Strange orange lights in the sky.

Five strange orange lights in formation, moving very quickly.

A bright orange light, the size of a helicopter. It looked like a flame

Two very bright glowing orange lights moving at very high speed.
